npm> Node Package Manger


////////package.json///////
> this is the entry point to the app
> it contains MetaData (Name,version,description)
> All the packages we use in the app
> Script (start, build,test)

// Step to generate package.json
** NodeJs must be installed in laptop
> Go inside the folder using cmd
> npm init
> Answer All the questions
> Type "yes"


// Step to install package
** NodeJs must be installed in laptop
> Go inside the folder using cmd
> npm i packageName/ npm install packageName

global dependency
> which will install in laptop irrespative of any folder
> Mainly package use for the purpose of starting the app

> open the cmd as Admin
> npm i -g packageName

npm i -g nodemon


